organic_results.title: School bureaucratization and alienation from high school
organic_results.snippet: The relationship between students' alienation from school and perceived school bureaucratization is examined in a sample of 18 high schools. The major goals of the study are to identify dimensions of bureaucracy and alienation, to determine the relationship of these dimensions to second-order, or integrating, factors, and to determine the relationships between the integrating factors of bureaucratic structure and alienation.
